      "amount": "0.25 tsp"
    },
    {
      "name": "Red onion",
      "amount": "1/4 medium",
      "notes": "thinly sliced"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and lay the pastry sheet flat.",
    "Spread the beaten egg and a drizzle of olive oil over the pastry.",
    "Arrange the sliced Cheddar, chopped parsley, thinly sliced red onion, and sprinkle chili flakes evenly on top.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper.",
    "Drizzle a little more olive oil over the cheese layer.",
    "Place in a preheated oven at 200°C and bake for 12 minutes or until golden and gooey.",
    "Remove from oven and let rest for 2 minutes before slicing.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy the fresh, spicy, and nourishing Australian Cheddar Bake."
  ],
